34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8

37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.

409 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
410 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;

412 template <typename T>
413 class WeakCallbackInfo {
414  public:
415  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
416 
417  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
418  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
419  Callback* callback)
420  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
421  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
422  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
423  }
424  }
425 
426  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
427  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
428  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
429 
430  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
431  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
432  return embedder_fields_[0];
433  }
434  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
435  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
436  return embedder_fields_[1];
437  }
438 
439  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
440  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
441  return callback_ != nullptr;
442  }
443 
444  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451 
452  private:
453  Isolate* isolate_;
454  T* parameter_;
455  Callback* callback_;
456  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
457 };

460 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
461 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
462 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
463 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
464 // possible to request a second pass callback.
465 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

676 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
677  public:
681  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
687  template <class S>
688  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
689  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
690  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
691  }
697  template <class S, class M2>
698  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
699  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
700  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
701  }
708  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
709  Copy(that);
710  }
711  template <class S, class M2>
712  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
713  Copy(that);
714  }
715  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
716  Copy(that);
717  return *this;
718  }
719  template <class S, class M2>
720  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
721  Copy(that);
722  return *this;
723  }
729  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
730  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
731  }
732 
733  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
734  template <class S>
735  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
736 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
737  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
738  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
739  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
740 #endif
741  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
742  }
743 
744  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
745  template <class S>
746  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
747  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
748  }

969 class ScriptOriginOptions {
970  public:
971  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
972  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
973  bool is_module = false)
974  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
975  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
976  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
977  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
978  : flags_(flags &
979  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
980

1182  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {

1184  BufferNotOwned,
1185  BufferOwned
1186  };
1187 
1188  CachedData()
1189  : data(NULL),
1190  length(0),
1191  rejected(false),
1192  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1193 
1194  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1195  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1196  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1197  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1198  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1199  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1200  ~CachedData();
1201  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1202  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1203  const uint8_t* data;
1204  int length;
1205  bool rejected;
1206  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1207 
1208  // Prevent copying.
1209  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1210  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1211  };

6372  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6373  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6374  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6375  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each

6385  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.

6388  // code line information which is returned from the
6389  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6390  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6391  void* user_data;

6427 enum RAILMode {
6428  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6429  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6430  // Throughput may be throttled.
6431  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6432  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6433  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6434  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.

6437  // in this mode.
6438  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,

6440  // turn off latency optimizations.
6441  PERFORMANCE_LOAD

8075 template <class T>
8076 class Maybe {
8077  public:
8078  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8079  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8080 
8084  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8085 
8090  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8091  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8092  return IsJust();
8093  }
8094 
8099  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8100  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8101  return value_;
8102  }
8103 
8108  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8109  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8110  }
8111 
8112  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8113  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8114  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8115  }
8116 
8117  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8118  return !operator==(other);
8119  }
8120 
8121  private:
8122  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8123  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8124 
8125  bool has_value_;
8126  T value_;
8127 
8128  template <class U>
8129  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8130  template <class U>
8131  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8132 };
8133

8135 template <class T>
8136 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8137  return Maybe<T>();
8138 }
8139 
8140 
8141 template <class T>
8142 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8143  return Maybe<T>(t);

8700  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8701  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8702  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8703  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8704 }
8705 
8706 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8707 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8708  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8709  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8710  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8711  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8712  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8713  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8714  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8715  }
8716  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8717  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8718  }
8719  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8720  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8721  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8722  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8723  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8724  //
8725  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8726  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8727  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8728  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8729  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8730  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8731  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8732  }
8733 };
8734 
8735 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8736 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8737  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8738  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8739  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8740  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8741  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8742  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8743  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8744  }
8745  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8746  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8747  }
8748  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8749  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8750  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8751  }
8752 };

9404 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9405 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9406  typedef internal::Object O;
9407  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9408  typedef internal::Internals I;
9409  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9410  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9411  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9412  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9413  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9414  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9415  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9416  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9417  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9418  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9419  }
9420 #endif
9421  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9422 }
9423 
9424 
9425 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9426 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9427  typedef internal::Object O;
9428  typedef internal::Internals I;
9429  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9430  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9431  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9432  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9433  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9434  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9435  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9436  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9437  }
9438 #endif
9439  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9440 }
